In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation declaring May 10, 2019, as Military Spouse Day. The proclamation acknowledges the important role that military spouses play in supporting their loved ones in the armed forces and expresses appreciation for their contributions. It highlights the challenges that military families face due to frequent relocations and the economic costs that military spouses often bear. The administration is committed to enhancing opportunities for military spouses, including promoting noncompetitive hiring authority and encouraging support from federal agencies and private companies. The article emphasizes the need for communities and individuals to support military spouses and raise awareness about resources available to them. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities.